 Nation, and he and I are soon to wed. We have two children, born through passion. Aenduina, my daughter is a Warrior. She has embraced the teachings of Innoruk. My son, Tresaeth has the makings of a fine Wizard, though both are young. My guild is my family, and within them I find comfort and peace through the hardest times. And if ever I am needed, for jewellery or companionship, or just to lend an ear, never hesitate to send me a tell. <br><br>-Tressa Dragonchild<br>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ubaddarshypertank.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BaddarsHypertank</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#B30000>(6/11/02 3:02:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For who we are shall not be shrouded in mystery...</span><hr size=1> /as Baddars<br><br>When i was but a small half-elf, i was taken under the wing of a strong and powerfull warrior. He went by the name of Ashbash. Under the ing of this powerfull warrior i learned the ways of being a tank, by killing things in the courtyard of Freeport. At the tender age of 7 circles my master and role model left me,a nd i was taken under the guidance of a lvl 60 cleric named Sicon. Under the guidance of this cleric i learned the ways of a &quot;hyper&quot;-tank, because of the way that he aided me into my cirlces between 10 and 20.<br>However the power and support of this powerfull Cleric left me to fend for myself at the age of 17 cirlces.<br><br>From this time on i learned the ways of the world myself and earned myself the name of Baddars Hypertank. My surname came from the fact that i was a hyper warrior under the guidance of Sicon.<br><br>At the age of 11 cirlces i joined draconis, a descision which i will never regret as the guild has helped me through many situations and i dont know where i would be without them.<br><br>Well thats my story.<br><br>Baddars Hypertank<br>Warrior the 29th cirlce<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bdraconisrampant.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=telefae>Telefae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 147<br> <font color=#B30000>(6/12/02 4:47:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For who we are shall not be shrouded in mystery...</span><hr size=1> An altar, bathed in a bright light from an unknown source was shining directly down onto the alter, on which lay a small child.<br><br>Three beings approached, two clothed in solid black robes, covering their whole, face and all.  The centre figure robed in a deathly green, gold and silver patterns glimmered as the robe shifted.  An unearthly glow eminating from his eyes, his breath cold and stale.<br><br>The two robed in black stood either side of the altar, and reached in to grab the child.  The light flashed, and slowly subsided, leaving the two figures laying mangled on the floor.<br><br>The remaining figure kneeled, and started chanting a strange chant, his lips moving, barely making a sound.  Slowly the light changed, from a bright white to a dark bluish-black.<br><br>The childs expression changed from that of innocence to that of intense hatred, his eyes changed from a light blue, to an unholy green.  The light penetrated his skin, turning the child blue from head to toe.<br><br>The figure finally reached in and grabbed the child, taking him from his position on the altar.<br><br>----------------------------------------<br><br>My coming of age brought great powers, the power of life is within my grasp, I can give it, or take it, at my will.  The roots of my being are revealed to me by my master, the robed figure.<br><br>----------------------------------------<br><br>A cult follower, the figure had released the demon Drach`nyen, a spirit entombed within the blade of a powerful general of a chaotic army, long gone, moved on to deeper battles, battles of will and spirit, the flesh long forgotten.<br><br>The demon Drach`nyen had possessed the child, infusing himself with the childs whole being, transforming him to the being he is today.<br><br>With each day he grows stronger, his ability to control life and death growing in intensity.<br><br>One day his power will grow to that of supremacy, and all shall bow before the might of Drach`nyen Souldevourer. <p>----------------------------------<br><br>Drachnyen Souldevourer<br>Necromancer of Innoruuk<br>Beloved of Kethryveris Souldevourer<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ukaminite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaminite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#B30000>(6/12/02 8:54:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For who we are shall not be shrouded in mystery...</span><hr size=1> /Sumalaen<br><br><br>I was born in Shar Vahl, son to the General of Shar Vahl's troops, Marmalaen, and Shilyaine, the high shaman of the shaman guild. <br><br>When I was but a wee kitten, my parents noticed I was strong and agile, that I was destined to be a great warrior. By my 11th season it was obvious to everyone that they were correct, and might I add that I was/am quite the heartbreaker and drunkard. <br><br>About a year after my birth, my brother Skann was born.  He was destined to be a bard. He had the voice of an angel, and although not quite as sexy as I, with his voice he was quite the heartbreaker as well. <br><br>One day out of the blue, a lot of strange people started arriving in Shar Vahl, and Skann found himself falling for a wood elven lass named Maypop (who can blame em? those Wood Elves and Barbarian females are hard to resist). A couple of weeks later, Skann was no where to be found. I asked his friends, they all said last the seen of him he was headed with Maypop towards Paludal Caverns. I went to investigate at my mother's and father's request. Last sighting of him on the moon was in the nexus at the Fawdar scion. I went and reported to my parents that I thought he had went to the new world, and that I would like to try and find him and explore the new world as well. <br><br>I bid my parents farewell, and headed out. I found my self in some place called Greater Faydark. I was amazed at all that I saw, the rich lush forest, the amazing tree city, and all the wood elven lasses running amuck. I asked around in the city and I was told that Maypop was seen traveling with one of my race headed to Freeport. I ran through Butcherblock Mountains to catch the boat, might I add that I saw some strange creatures there called Dwarves, most of their lasses were pleasing to the eye, except some of them had beards. Yuck! <br><br>I finally made it to the boat and got on. I got sea sick on the way. I hate boats. This was my first boat ride ever and hopefully my last. Did I mention that I hate boats? Anyway, I made it to Freeport and asked around about Skann and Maypop. I turned up many leads, but I have yet to find Skann. <br><br>I kept wandering about joining a few groups of adventurers along the way. I never truly felt at home with any of them so I left. Then one day A dark elf Necromancer that I befriended in my journeys, Kaminite, told me of this wonderful group of people that called themselves Draconis Rampant. I joined up with them, and very soon I knew that they were my family, that this was my home. <br><br>Draconis and I have had many perils and adventures, all in all a great time. Every time I or one of our friends needed help Draconis has been there. We are a tight nit family, and I think I speak for us all when I say if you need help we will be there. Hail Draconis, my friends, my family, and my home! <br><br>/Sumalaen<br><br><br>Just remember everyone, that I am damn sexy and I am The Ladies Cat™.<br> <p><center><font color="black" font="Comic Sans MS"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=186435><img src="http://www.geocities.com/character8in/sum7.gif"></a><br>Damn Sexy Vah Shir Warrior of the 48th level</br></font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/usnootchybootchies.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SnootchyBootchies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#B30000>(6/13/02 8:27:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For who we are shall not be shrouded in mystery...</span><hr size=1> /Snootchies<br><br> Long ago a horrible battle took place in Kithicor Forest. The Lord of Hate himself stepped foot into the mortal realm and ignited a devistating battle that forever changed the land. Many rushed into battle to stop the evil god and his minions, one family that rushed into battle wielding spellbooks filled with arcane knowledge were the Delanooch, a powerful Halfling family respected and honored by all others within the Vale and its surronding lands. The minions of hate knew well of the family's reputation and made sure to strike them down quickly. As the troops from the Vale rushed into the forest, they were ambushed by a group of skilled Dark Elf assassins. They quickly spotted their targets and made their attack only to be denied their victory and sent to the afterlife. The battle raged on until the troops were face to face with the Lord of Hate. As they prepared to use all they had to stop him they were ambushed and destroyed ending the name of Delanooch.... or so they thought. Unknown to even their evil lord, one Delanooch still lived. The youngest of the family, Don Juan, had been left in the hands of the town druids while the family went to fight for their homeland.<br><br> Years later, the druids of Rivervale had raised Don Juan to be a mighty druid. He eagerly awaited the day he would see the world and find his family. The druids had lied to him. He had been told his family served the Vale in a secret quest that would take many years to complete. On the day he had learned all he could learn from the druids, they broke the truth to young Don.<br><br> Learning of his families fate, Don Juan's heart filled with anger and desire for only one thing. To gain all the power Karana had to offer him, so that he may destroy the forces of hate. He set out upon the world of Norrath, taking the name Snootchies Bootchies, so no agents of hate would hear the name of a family they believe long dead.<br><br>  Not long after his travels had began, Snootchies met a valiant warrior by the name of Wachu. He was then brought into Wachu's family, Draconis Rampant. To this day Snootchies strives to become more powerful by the day, but his primary concern is not the vengance of his old family as it once was. He now lives for his new family, the family of Draconis, and seeing that all his family live long happy lives, while being the sexiest Halfling ever to grace Norrath! <br><br>  Ladies of Norrath lookout(especially those high elven chanters, ya know who ya are <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ! Snootchies Bootchies is comin at ya! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/bdraconisrampant.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kethryveris>Kethryveris</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#B30000>(6/14/02 12:12:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For who we are shall not be shrouded in mystery...</span><hr size=1> / Kethryveris<br><br>Behold a child of darkness and hate....or is she?<br>Much of my early life is unknown to me...why? Because the god Innoruuk is fond of pain and hate.  As one of the first things I can remember I was raised in the guilds lower chambers mastering the spells and theories of necromancy with but one goal.  To set out upon the face of Norrath and cause chaos.  But , you say , Innorruuk is not a god of Chaos.  I tell you now that his chaos is so subtle you will not see his hand untill too late.  Raised as I was I had no friends no family to speak of.. but within my first few seasons in the outside I found both.  I found a friend in Drachnyen, a necromancer of no small skill and a family in his Guild, Draconis Rampant.  As I grew in my seasons I began to see the subtle hand I spoke of, I was not here to cause chaos on a large scale... no only for one was I here.  Drachnyen.  I freely admidt I have turned his world upside down and made him question his hatred...or rather the hate if the demon within.  For within Drach lies the mortal soul of the child on the altar, not destroyed as his mentor thought... simply subsumed by the demon.  Now Innoruuk is a jealous god and to have one of HIS vessels taken from him has simply not sat well.  So I have been sent..armed with a most unlikely weapon, to free him.  Each day that we are together I chip at the demon, wear him down...but for a long time I could not find Drachnyen and so feared my task undone and feared also the wrath Innoruuk would show me.  But Drachnyen has returned to me...the demon losing a battle to the child within.. though he knows it not..and so I continue to fight the battle and create chaos with the most unlikely weapon you will ever see a Dark Elf Necromance wield..............love.<br><br><br>Kethryveris Souldevourer<br>Necromancer and child of Innoruuk<br>Beloved of Drachnyen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uwarrl1870.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Warrl1870</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#B30000>(6/14/02 6:14:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For who we are shall not be shrouded in mystery...</span><hr size=1> /Warrl <br>  I was born in the frozen tundra of everfrost where my family trade was trapping. At an early age my parents started teaching me the ways of the animals we hunted, one day they went out to check the lines an left me to to finish scraping the latest set of mammoth hides we had gathered. That was the last I ever saw of them, I was left alone in the frozen wilds. A lone beast lord of our clan found me and taught me the ways of the beast lord and brought me to the altars of the Tribunal. It was there that I pledged my life to dealing out there justice to those deserving of it. I made my way south to plains of Karana and east to Freeport. along the way I heard many speak of a group of people always ready to lend a hand to those in need and started searching. after about 10 seasons of searching the lovely woodelf lass Pipette found me and we talked of her family called Draconis Rampant and I knew I had found a family that I would be proud to serve.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/umistiirainbowchaser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mistii Rainbowchaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#B30000>(6/15/02 11:42:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> For who we are shall not be shrouded in mystery...</span><hr size=1> Sometimes the life of a Barbarian in Norrath can lend itself to a somewhat soap opera like life.  It has for me...I was born in Halas, to parents who were fishermen.  We spent many a long day fishing, cleaning the fish and taking them to market to sell.  It was a smelly terrible job, and I always swore to myself that I would not endure that kind of life when I was on my own.  At around 10 circles, I went to visit relatives in the Western Plains of Karana, there, I met a lovely man by the name of Shayman.  He was to be my true love (or was he...).  We hunted together many a time, I, with my faithful pup at my side, and he with the spirit of The Shamen of Justice pulsing through him.  I was certain that we were destined to be.  Then, around my 19th circle, he was not hunting with me nearly as frequently as he had been...my attention was diverted, and I knew then that we were not meant to be.  I met the true love of my life, my darling Warrl Loreweaver.  I had not yet promised myself to Shayman in terms of marriage, but Warrl and I waited for so long to plan our upcoming marriage out of fairness to the other.  Finally after a very long night of hunti