tizens of the Vale were wondering if they could hold many more attacks from the enemy much longer.  For this very reason, many of the newer families that entered the Vale were not allowed to study the skills of the druid, yet learn the skills of battle by training with sword and shield.  The Malkieri family was one of the strongest families that went through warrior training, and the mayor even recognized my family as one of the official guardian families of the Vale.  As a member of this family, I was assigned to protect important people within the city.  Over time, I have become a personal guardian of Tressa Dragonchild, an important and highly recognized individual.<br>           While on a journey with Tressa one day, I met a strong druid by the name of Don Juan Delanooch.  I thought the family had fallen, but when he began talking about how sexy he was (trademark of the family<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) I knew he was a Delanooch. He has joined the ranks of Draconis as a good friend of mine, yet he is not a member of the Malkieri family.  I hope people now look at me and say,&quot; There goes Wachu Malkieri, halfling warrior.&quot;   <br>     <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ustormyfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>stormyfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#B30000>(6/17/02 12:25:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For who we are shall not be shrouded in mystery...</span><hr size=1> /Raiderarc<br><br><br>In the open plains of the Karanas, I was a young warrior hunting my way through to rivers.  I've heard my parents have been killed by bandits while they were buying some household products Halas did not have.  Rage was the first of foes I've met and won my first battle.  I picked up a sword and registered at the warrior and recieved some traing.  My master taught me some basic skills but not enough to survive out side of our Tundra.  At my fifth season I had enough and wanted revenge.  I stumbled through the tundra to and made haste through the stench filled burrow of the gnolls.  Ran though the hills of Qeynos and made it to the east part of the Karanas.  I tried to find bandits with no luck.  After three season I came upon a camp of bandits laughing and drinking.  They glared at me as I passed by and seemed like i wasn't some worhty enough for them.  As I walked by I found a female bandit with my mother's braclet.  With Fury and Anger i charged the camp!  I tried to fight my best downing 2 bandits before I was overtaken.  I was captured and to be excuted by haning.  When the day came I though to be with my parents soon.  As they pushed me to the ropes a loud crack of thunder shook the groud and waves of ice poured through their camp.  The bandits ran to their attacker and one by one was slain, sometimes 3-4 would fall.  Minutes later a halfing walked up to me, healed me and released me.  I asked why he didnt' let me die after  explained the death of my parents.  He scolded me and said you live today, grow stronger tomorrow to avenge them.  But then I had no where to go and out of food.  He being the most genorus of all offered me a home in his city of Rivervale.  In Rivervale he arranged that the Guardians of Vale to teach me skills.  He himself taught me to read, to write to live.  He now I call Father. I grown strong with this teachings and I learned the bandit with my mother's braclets was still alive.  I went back to EK and found her.  That pittiful being begged for her life and all I can think of was my parents asking for theirs.  Now all the bandits that held resposbilty is dead and I'm at peace<br><br>As for my current family I will explain. I was the first of many of Stormhunter's &lt;Father&gt; adopted childern.  Second was Feung but has left to be with the monks in Qeynos.  Third was a poor child halfling theive that recived some heavy punishment for pick pocketing the mayor.  Knavin was rescued by father after father convinced the mayor he can change.  Fourth was a child gnome of hate named Shinmei.  He became a knight of darkness to avenge his exile.  Couldn't belive father allowed it..&lt;sigh&gt;  A fifth was just recnetly taken in named Vironci, his first daughter.  While father and me was reinforcing the halflings in nek. forest we came accross a dispectble crying baby.  Being soft hearted and loving of all nature's creations &lt;if Darkelves were of nature's creation&gt; he took her in.  Strangly she smiled.... now she has grown strong....and I dislike her much...but she loves father much...<br>Well that is the story of me and my family<br><br>Raiderarc Stormraider<br>Champion of Stormhunter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#767676><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/uwulfric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wulfric</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#B30000>(6/19/02 5:59:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/fdraconisrampantfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For who we are shall not be shrouded in mystery...</span><hr size=1> Savawulf&gt;<br><br>For who I am will always be shrouded in mystery....<br><br>Sad to say my past is confused by miscellaneous alter-egos, all of which have been a learning experience to make  me the ranger that I am today, and the great ranger that I hope to be.  For if you believe in reincarnation, then I could say that my original incarnation was that of a half-elf rogue under the name of Wulfric Rennison who has a long and sordid history of his own, most of which is told in an epic poem which has yet to be published in any major format.  Wulfric was and is a great rogue who was adopted into the family known formerly as Hecates Wrath, under the guidance of the guild leader, Vveraksizz Bloodscale. However, internal turmoil broke the Hecates family and the members scattered to all directions following their own paths. After this break up, Wulfric went into hiding and the next incarnation was born under the guise of a wood elf druid named Raido Covenfall.  Historically, the records would tell you that Raido was, in truth, a good friend to Wulfric Rennison, each using the other's skills to obtain new armor and equipment occasionally.  Raido enjoyed his own familial bond with the ones known as Amicus Concordiam, And it is through this persona that he made the acquaintance of one human ranger known only as Profian.  It was a rare occasion in Norrath when Profian would make his appearance, and in his 18th cycle, Profian decided to end his life, though before he went, he promised all his worldly possessions to the wise druid.  Yet Raido had not the space nor the strength to carry such heavy equipment and it was then that the ego known as Savawulf was born.  Although, I came into life as the proverbial mule, I have taken on a unique life of my own, finding my place, and creating my own identity in the family known as Draconis Rampant.  It feels good to be welcomed so warmly, and I only hope I can live up to the great expectations of the wonderous family I see around me.  <br><br>Draconis Forever. <br><br>Savawulf Tageric<br>half-elf ranger <p><Insert Signature Here></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="to